name: Protein Pizza
steps: Add the flours, water, instant yeast, salt, and olive oil to the bowl

name: Protein Pizza
steps: Transfer the dough to a lightly oiled container about 3-4 times the size of the dough.

name: Protein Pizza
steps: Divide the dough into 5 equal pieces, 180 grams each.

name: Protein Pizza
steps: Preheat the oven to 500°F about 1 hour into the proofing process.

name: Protein Pizza
steps: Once the dough is proofed, gently spread the dough into an oval shape about 11-12 inches long.

name: Protein Pizza
steps: Transfer the shaped pinsa into a pizza peel and then, add the toppings of your choice.

name: Protein Pizza
steps: Place the pinsa into the preheat oven and bake for 3-6 minutes or until crisp.

name: Protein Pizza
steps: Let the pinsa cool slightly before slicing.

name: Exotic Ginger Cumin Chicken
steps: In large saucepan heat 2 tsp oil over medium heat. Add half of the chicken and cook 3 minutes until brown. Remove from pan and set aside. Repeat with remaining chicken.

name: Exotic Ginger Cumin Chicken
steps: Add remaining oil to pan; add garlic, onion, and ginger. Reduce heat to medium and cook, stirring constantly for 5 minutes or until soft. Stir in cayenne, cumin, and turmeric; saute for 1 minute.

name: Exotic Ginger Cumin Chicken
steps: Stir in stock, tomatoes, tomato paste, and sugar; return chicken to pan. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.

name: Exotic Ginger Cumin Chicken
steps: Stir in yogurt and simmer 2 minutes.

name: Fried Rice
steps: Start by bringing some water to a boil in a pot.

name: Fried Rice
steps: Preheat a wide non-stick pan over medium high heat and add some vegetable oil along with 2 beaten eggs.

name: Fried Rice
steps: Wipe out pan, add more oil, and then add the shrimp (or the protein of your choice). Once cooked, set aside in the bowl with the eggs.

name: Fried Rice
steps: Add 2 cloves of crushed garlic and cook for about 30 seconds before adding 4 cups of cooked white rice.

name: Fried Rice
steps: Turn the heat to high and let the whole thing saute. Break up any big chunks of rice and cook for about 3-5 minutes.

name: Fried Rice
steps: Add your eggs and protein back into the mix and top with some sesame oil and thinly sliced scallions.

name: Fried Rice
steps: Reduce the heat to low and add some sesame seeds. Mix to combine.

name: Fried Rice
steps: Finish it off by adding 1 Tbsp of butter and mixing that to combine.

name: Ukrainian Borscht Soup
steps: Peel, grate and/or slice all vegetables (keeping sliced potatoes in cold water to prevent browning until ready to use then drain).
column14: drop the whole tomatoes into boiling water for 2 minutes

name: Ukrainian Borscht Soup
steps: Heat a large soup pot (5 1/2 Qt or larger) over medium/high heat and add 2 Tbsp olive oil.
column14: drop the whole tomatoes into boiling water for 2 minutes

name: Ukrainian Borscht Soup
steps: Add grated beets and sauté 10 minutes, stirring occasionally until beets are softened.
column14: drop the whole tomatoes into boiling water for 2 minutes

name: Ukrainian Borscht Soup
steps: Add 8 cups broth and 2 cups water.
column14: drop the whole tomatoes into boiling water for 2 minutes

name: Ukrainian Borscht Soup
steps: Add sliced potatoes and sliced carrots then cook for 10-15 minutes or until easily pierced with a fork.
column14: drop the whole tomatoes into boiling water for 2 minutes

name: Ukrainian Borscht Soup
steps: While potatoes are cooking, place a large skillet over medium/high heat and add 2 Tbsp oil.
column14: drop the whole tomatoes into boiling water for 2 minutes

name: Ukrainian Borscht Soup
steps: Add chopped onion, celery and bell pepper. Saute stirring occasionally until softened and lightly golden (7-8 minutes).
column14: drop the whole tomatoes into boiling water for 2 minutes

name: Ukrainian Borscht Soup
steps: Add 4 Tbsp Ketchup and stir fry for 30 seconds then transfer to the soup pot to continue cooking with the potatoes.
column14: drop the whole tomatoes into boiling water for 2 minutes

name: Ukrainian Borscht Soup
steps: When potatoes and carrots reach desired softness, add optional ingredients from the list.

steps: Simmer for an additional 2-3 minutes and add more spices to taste.

name: Beef Jerky
steps: Slice beef into ¼" (½ cm) thick strips. Small chunks, about ¾" (2 cm), of stewing beef may also be used. If possible, cut along the grain of the meat rather than across it. It may be easier to freeze the meat before attempting to cut it, as this will stop the meat pulling and deforming so easily.

name: Beef Jerky
steps: Marinate meat in overnight, or at least for an hour or two.

name: Beef Jerky
steps: Place meat on racks and dry in a food dehydrator at 145 °F (63 °C) for 6-8 hours. May be dried in a 150 °F (65 °C) oven with foil-covered racks. In oven, turn meat over 3-4 hours into drying time and reduce temperature to 130 °F (55 °C).
